The paper deals with deep metric learning applied to computer vision tasks, specifically zero-shot image retrieval and clustering. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for optimizing a robust metric, which involves an adversarial training approach. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of various datasets, indicating that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image retrieval, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
